Unlike Sorting Signed Permutations by Reversals problem which has an exact polynomial-time algorithm, the Reversal Distance for Signed Strings problem is NP-hard [15]. Chen et al. [4] proved that Reversal Distance for Signed Strings is NP-hard even if we consider the simplest case where at most two replicas are allowed for each gene (duplicated genes). The authors also showed that the Reversal Distance for Signed Strings and the Minimum Common String Partition (MCSP) problems are related. The Reversal Distance for Unsigned Strings and Reverse MCSP [11] problems are also related. Based on this information, an approximation algorithm for the Reversal Distance in Signed and Unsigned Strings problems were presented with a factor of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
